> I think it's a great idea to have a better execution and development
> environment than what I use for LILO (16 bit assembler is a pain).
So write in C. The Dev86 toolkit - thats the stuff as86/ld86 as shipped are
prehistoric versions of - has a C compiler. The boot block for loading
ELKS off a minix fs disk is in 16bit C for example.
The tools all exist.
